Playbook - is a manual that provides details about any operational action.
-- is a tool also used to know which tools will be used in response to a security incidents.

Incident Response - An organization's quick attempt to identify an attack, contain the damage, and correct the effects of a security breach.

6 Phase of Incident Response Playbook;

Preparation - Preparation in an attempt to mitigate the likelihood, risks, and impact of a security incident by documenting procedures, establishing staffing plans, and educating users.

Detection and Analysis - is to detect and analyze events using defined processes and technology.
-- using appropriate tools and strategies helps SEC analyst determine whether a breach has occured and analyze its possible damges.

Containment - is to prevent further damage and reduce the immediate impact of a security incident. 
-- takes action to contain an incident and minimize damages.

Eradication and recovery; 
-- the complete removal of an incident artifacts so that an organization can return to normal operation.
-- security professionals eliminate artifacts of the incident by removing malicious code and mitigating vulnerabilities.
-- IT restoration by restoring the environment.

Post incident Activity - includes documenting the incident, informing organizational leadership, and applying lessons learned to ensure that an organization is better prepared to handle future incidents.
-- determining the root cause of an incident and implementing various updates or improvements to the software.

Coordination - involves reporting incidents and sharing information, throughout the incident reponse process, based oon the organization's established standards.
-- Coordination is important.

Purpose and Benefits of a Playbook;

A Playbook is invaluable for guiding an analyst through the necessary actions to properly address the alert.

First Action of a Playbook;
- Assess the alert
- Determining if the alert is actually valid by identifying why the alert was generated by the SIEM.

Second Action of a Playbook;
- It outlines the actions and tools to use to the contain malware and reduce further damages.

Third Action of a Playbook;
- Eliminating all traces of the incident and restore the affected systems back to normal operations.

Fourth Action of a Playbook;
- Instruct the analyst to perform various post-incident activities and coordination efforts with the security team.
- Reporting and communicating the security incidents to the stakeholders or reporting the incident to the appropriate authorities, like the U.S. Federal Bureau of Investigations or other agencies that investigate cyber crimes.




